Three people were killed at dawn Friday after the car they were travelling collided head on with a bus at Bobaracho shopping centre along Kisii, Keroka Highway. The probox car was travelling from Kegati to Kisii town while the Ena Coach bus was heading to Nairobi when the accident occurred near the entrance to Musa Nyandusi Secondary school. No bus passenger was injured in the 5 am incident . Area chief Alexander Nyakinyua told the Star said theÂ  driver of the car was trying to avoid a pothole when he rammed into the oncoming Ena Coach bus. "All the three male passengers aboard including the driver died on the spot," Nyakinyua said. The bodies have since been moved to Kisii Teaching and Referral Hospital morgue.